(32, 5, 'confrontations', 'Confrontations', '<p><span class="whiteheader">Confrontations: Films Against Violence and Intolerance</span></p>\n<hr size="2" width="100%" />\n<p><em>&nbsp;A selection of films from the Confrontations competition at the 2009 interfilm Berlin Short Film Festival</em><br />\n</p>\n<br />\n<span class="uppercase">Dogs Bar<br />\n54 Acland St, st kilda<br />\nsunday 30 may, 12PM- 1.30PM</span><br />\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The aim of the Confrontations program, an annual highlight at interfilm Berlin is to tell meaningful stories that confront the audience and call for our empathy. </p>\n<p>\nThis selection refreshingly includes a number of comedies which in their own particular way manage to deal respectfully with such sensitive subjects. </p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Curated by Heinz Hermanns and Stephanie Hofmaier – interfilm Berlin Short Film Festival.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<hr size="2" width="100%" />\n<p>SESSIONS AT THE DOGS BAR:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>This year the iconic Dogs Bar presents two very special screenings. </p>\n<p>Pull up a pew, grab a drink and make yourself comfortable in the Dogs Bar''s intimate private screening room.<br />\n</p>\n<p>Bookings:</p>\n<p>Phone 03 8534 3020</p>\n<p>$10 per person.</p>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<p><em></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;<img src="/Uploads/19_Dogs%20Bar.jpg" alt="" border="0" width="120" height="60" /></p>\n<hr size="2" width="100%" />\n<p><em>The Confrontations Session includes:</em><br />\n</p>', '2010-05-01 10:47:26', '2010-05-05 15:25:55'),
(33, 5, 'introduction', 'Introduction', '<p><span class="whiteheader">International Program</span></p>\n<hr size="2" width="100%" />\nFilm is an immediate, graphic, forceful and emotional form of communication and this program gives Australian audiences and filmmakers the opportunity to experience some of the most memorable, thoughtful, quirky and powerful films from the international repertoire of shorts from the past few years.<br />\n<br />\nThis year you will see a selection of films sourced through one of the world’s most prestigious short film festivals interfilm Berlin, including the best of the 2009 German, Netherlands and Confrontations programs as well as a special program to mark the 20th anniversary of the fall of the Berlin Wall.<br />\n<p>\n</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>To hear more about interfilm Berlin sales and distribution and to gain valuable insight into what Australian filmmakers can do to maximise international screening opportunities, don’t miss the international Film Festivals Forum, Friday 28 May, 6.30pm – 7.30pm.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<hr size="2" width="100%" />\n<p class="orangeheader">&nbsp;international guests<br />\n</p>\n<p class="uppercase">St Kilda Film Festival warmly welcomes our special guests:</p>\n<p class="uppercase">&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span class="uppercase">Matthias Groll </span></p>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<p><img alt="" src="/Uploads/Matthias Groll.jpg" width="150" height="150" /><br />\n</p>\n<p>\n</p>\n<p><em></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>New Media Strategies, Public Relations &amp; Curator interfilm Berlin Short Film Festival.</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Matthias studied Communication in Berlin where he currently lives. In 1998 his book ‘Das Digital’ was published and, specialising in new media, has since written for many major newspaper and magazines.</p>\n<p>\nHe began working for interfilm Berlin in 1997 and was Head of Distribution from 2000 – 2006. </p>\n<p>Matthias curated the ‘Focus on Eastern&nbsp; Front/ Western Front’ program for the 2009 interfilm Berlin Festival – a selection of these films are included in the St Kilda Film Festival ‘Berlin: The Wall and Beyond’ program. Matthias will also be hosting ‘Inside The Wall’ at the Dog’s Bar.</p>\n<br />\n<hr size="2" width="100%" />\n<p>&nbsp;<span class="uppercase">Hanro Smitsman</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<em></em>\n<p>&nbsp;<img alt="" src="/Uploads/Hanro Smitsman.jpg" width="150" height="150" /></p>\n<p><em></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Multi award winning film and television writer and director from the Netherlands. </em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n</p>\n<p>In 2005, Hanro Smitsman’s film Engel en Broer (screening in the St Kilda Film Festival Dutch films Session, Friday 28 May, 7.30pm-9pm ) won the Cinema Prize for Short Film at the Avanca Film Festival. Many of his subsequent films have also been award winners at numerous festivals including the Berlin International Film Festival for which he won the prestigious ‘Golden Bear Award’, the Brooklyn Film Festival, the Palm Springs International Short Film Festival, the Flanders International Film Festival, the Nederlands Film Festival and the Cinema tous ecrans Festival in Geneva. He has worked on both short and feature length films as well as television.</p>', '2010-05-03 16:22:29', '2010-05-07 09:21:23'),
(34, 6, 'under-the-radar', 'Under the Radar', '<p><span class="whiteheader">Under the Radar</span></p>\n<hr size="2" width="100%" />\n<p><span class="uppercase">The Palace George Cinemas</span></p>\n<p class="uppercase">133-135 fitzroy st, st kilda <br />\n</p>\n<span class="uppercase">\nWednesday 26 May, 6pm - 7.20pm<br />\n</span>\n<p><span class="uppercase">FREE EVENT</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\nThe City of Port Phillip Youth Services and The FReeZa Collective presents a Youth Short Film Competition – providing an opportunity for young filmmakers to show their work in a nationally recognised and respected film festival. <br />\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Entries have been received from all over Australia and a number will compete to win the Under the Radar Best Youth Film Award.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\nThis event is fully supervised, smoke, alcohol and drug-free.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><img alt="" src="/Uploads/Under the Radar_RESIZED.jpg" width="200" height="270" /><br />\n&nbsp;</p>', '2010-05-03 17:20:55', '2010-05-18 15:13:42'),
(35, 6, 'armed-dangerous', 'Armed & Dangerous', '<p><span class="whiteheader">Armed and Dangerous</span></p>\n<hr size="2" width="100%" />\n<p class="uppercase"><span class="uppercase">The Palace George Cinemas</span></p>\n<p><span class="uppercase">133-135 fitzroy st, st kilda</span> <br />\n</p>\n<span class="uppercase">\nThursday 27 May, 1pm - 3pm <br />\nFREE EVENT</span><br />\n<br />\n<p>\nBookings T: 9510 5444 </p>\n<p>or E: fcramp@iellen.org.au </p>\n<p>\nW: armed-and-dangerous.tv</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n</p>\n<p><em>Presented by Blue SKYS</em>. Now in its sixth year!</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>\n</p>\n<p>The showcase of short films made by and for schools, community groups and young people involved in media education and training.</p>\n<p>\nA must see for anyone involved in film, media and youth development.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;<img alt="" src="/Uploads/Armed &amp; Dangerous.jpg" width="378" height="273" /></p>', '2010-05-03 17:21:08', '2010-05-04 22:35:29'),
(36, 12, 'latest-news', 'Latest News', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<span class="">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<span class="">\n<p><span class="" style="font-size: 18pt"> </span></p>\n<p><span class="" style="font-size: 18pt">2013 St Kilda Film Festival</span><span class="" style="font-size: 18pt"><br />\n<br />\nCALL FOR ENTRIES<br />\n</span><span class="" style="font-size: 18pt;">OPENS 1 OCTOBER</span> <br />\n<br />\n<br />\nVisit us in October to get full submission details and technical requirements, and register your film for the 2013 Festival.<br />\n<br />\n</p>\n</span>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</span>\n<p>Competition categories are: <br />\n<br />\n</p>\n<span class="orange">\n<p>St Kilda Film Festival short film competition<br />\n<br />\nSoundKILDA Australian music video competition<br />\n<br />\n</p>\n<p>Under the Radar - Emerging filmmakers under 21</p>\n</span>\n<p><strong><br />\n<br />\n</strong></p>\n<p>In 2013 the Festival will screen the Top 100 short film entries  received, and the competition is always fierce. The short film competition  awards over $40,000 worth of cash and in-kind craft awards, including a  $10,000 prize for Best Short Film! <br />\n<br />\n</p>\n<p>The Festival also features the SoundKILDA Australian Music Video  Competition where prizes are awarded in four categories, Best Music  Video, Best Independent Music Video, Best Music Video - Animation and  the special Audience Award voted for and presented the night of the  screening.<br />\n<br />\n</p>\n<p class="orange">St Kilda Film Festival celebrates its 30th anniversary in 2013. <br />\nWe hope you can join us for the party.<br />\n<br />\n</p>\n<br />\n<p> </p>\n<br />\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2010-05-03 17:43:42', '2012-08-09 15:16:52'),
(75, 13, 'under-21s:-under-the-radar', 'Under 21s: Under the Radar', '<p><span style="text-decoration: underline" class="whiteheader">UNDER THE RADAR - under 21''s youth short film competition</span></p>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline" class="whiteheader"><br />\n</span></p>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline" class="whiteheader"><img alt="" src="/Uploads/Under-the-Radar-Logo.jpg" width="200" height="385" /><br />\n</span></p>\n<p><span style="line-height: 19px; text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 19px"><u><br />\n</u></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span class="whiteheader">Entries close March 1st 2012</span></p>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.portphillip.vic.gov.au/under-the-radar.htm" target="_blank">Click here for more information and to download APPLICATION FORM and TERMS &amp; CONDITIONS</a></p>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<p>The City of Port Philip Youth Services will be hosting a under 21''s open entry category in this year''s St Kilda Film Festival.</p>\n<p><br />\nOver the past few years it has been noted that there is a growing number of young filmmakers producing shorts. Although, the St Kilda Film Festival is an open entry competition it is often difficult for young people to compete against more experienced film makers of an older age. This category will be solely dedicated to the work that is being produced by young filmmakers in Australia; films that have been produced outside Australia will not be included. </p>\n<p><br />\nThis category in the St Kilda Film Festival provides an opportunity for young filmmakers to show their work in an internationally recognised film festival. This opportunity will encourage young film makers to pursue their craft further and potentially produce future stars of cinema both in front of and behind the camera.</p>\n<p>2011 Winner ''<em>The Venting Place'' </em>Directed and Produced by Natalie James<br />\n2010 Winner ''<em>Charlotte</em>'' Directed by Zoe Coldham, Produced by Bethany Milkins<br />\n2009 Winner <em>''Wax Wings''</em> Directed and Produced by Grace Louey <br />\n2008 Winner ''<em>Mona</em>'' Directed by Charlotte Rose Hamlyn and Produced by David Thring</p>\n<p><br />\nThis is a FReeZA event, alcohol, smoke and drug free event.<br />\nFor more information please contact Martin Goffin Youth Engagement and Participation Officer on 03 9209 6167</p>\n', '2011-01-18 09:56:41', '2011-11-09 15:11:18'),
