uzet)<br />\n2000 Pozieres (Dir. Wain Fimeri)<br />\n1998 Bouganville: Our Island, Our Fight (Dir. Wayne Coles-Janess)</span><br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<span class="page_boldheading">Best New Director</span><br />\n<span class="page_text">2</span><span class="page_text">004 Corrie Jones (Victim)<br />\n2003 Puven Pather (The Shot)<br />\n2002 Nicholas Tomnay (The Host)<br />\n2001 Catriona McKensie (Road)<br />\n2000 Patrick Hughes (The Director)<br />\n1998 Marzena Domaradzka (Crouching at the Door)<br />\n</span><br />\n<br />\n<span class="page_boldheading">Most Positive Image of Age </span><br />\n<span class="page_text">2010 Primo Bacio (Dir. Sarah Vassilas/Prod. Sarah Vassilas)<br />\n2009 Lover’s Walk (Dir. Abigail Hargrave/Prod. Abigail Hargrave)<br />\n2008 Nana (Dir. Warwick Thornton/Prod. Kath Shelper)<br />\n2007 Pop’s Dream (Dir. Bronwyn Purvis/Prod. Christopher Saunders)<br />\n2006 Butterfly Man (Dir. Samantha Rebillet/Prod. Justin Davies)</span><br />\n<p>&nbsp;<br />\n</p>\n<br />\n<p><br />\n</p>', '2012-09-18 17:02:12', '2014-10-14 08:19:44'),
(118, 19, 'soundkilda---terms-conditions', 'SoundKILDA - Terms & Conditions', '<span class="page_heading">SOUNDKILDA TERMS &amp; CONDITIONS</span><br />\n<br />\n<span class="page_text"><br />\n1. Only Australian entries are eligible for the SoundKILDA  competition. If  you are unsure of eligibility, please contact the Festival office on 03 9209 6490 or email <a href="&#109;&#97;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;&#58;&#102;&#105;&#108;&#109;&#102;&#101;&#115;&#116;&#64;&#112;&#111;&#114;&#116;&#112;&#104;&#105;&#108;&#108;&#105;&#112;&#46;&#118;&#105;&#99;&#46;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#46;&#97;&#117;">filmfest@portphillip.vic.gov.au</a><br />\n<br />\n2. The producer grants the St Kilda Film Festival the rights to: (a) Exhibit the film in the SoundKILDA section of the St Kilda Film Festival and any subsequent tour (b) Reproduce the film for inclusion as part of a compilation (c) Exhibit the production either in part or in total for promotional purposes<br />\n<br />\n3. The producer warrants to the St Kilda Film Festival that they have obtained all the necessary permissions to enter this film and that the film does not infringe the rights, including copyright, of any third party. This includes use of music and literary material (ie if your film is based on a novel or poem).<br />\n<br />\n4. Entries will not be considered valid until the entry fee has been paid<br />\n<br />\n5. Entries must be received or postmarked by 5pm, Thursday 31 January 2013<br />\n<br />\n6. Entries may not be withdrawn after Friday 15 March 2013<br />\n<br />\n7. If your film is selected for the competition you will be sent a letter of confirmation (via email) by Monday 1 April 2013. Film Prints, tape masters or hard drives must be received by Friday 12 April 2013.<br />\n<br />\n8. Materials submitted in the initial entry process will not be returned. Screening copies of films selected to screen in SoundKILDA will be returned to the nominated address on the entry form after the Festival. Please make sure this address is correct and if any details change please email us at <a href="&#109;&#97;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;&#58;&#102;&#105;&#108;&#109;&#102;&#101;&#115;&#116;&#64;&#112;&#111;&#114;&#116;&#112;&#104;&#105;&#108;&#108;&#105;&#112;&#46;&#118;&#105;&#99;&#46;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#46;&#97;&#117;">filmfest@portphillip.vic.gov.au</a> to let us know.<br />\n<br />\n9. The St Kilda Film Festival will pay for the return of participating films for the Festival within Australia. Forwarding of prints to international destinations will be at the filmmaker’s expense. Forwarding films to the Festival is the responsibility of the filmmaker.<br />\n<br />\n10. Whilst the St Kilda Film Festival will take due care of prints or tapes entered, the Festival will not be responsible for any loss and/or damage to prints, DVDs or tapes while they are in the possession of the Festival or any of the cinemas hosting the Festival or the Tour.<br />\n<br />\n11. The St Kilda Film Festival will tour a selection of films featured in SoundKILDA nationally from July through to September. All films entered in the St Kilda Film Festival must be available for touring. Tour films will be returned after the tour concludes.<br />\n<br />\n12. The St Kilda Film Festival only screens productions finished on 35mm, 16mm, Digibeta, HDCAM and digital harddrive. We do NOT screen from Beta SP. Please see the <a href="http://localhost/stkildafilm/callforentries/page-119/screening-formats-audio-specs">Screening Formats &amp; Audio Specifications</a> page for more information. To ensure your entry is screened correctly, you must include screening gauge and ratio details as requested on the entry form.</span><br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<p>     	</p>', '2012-09-18 14:42:13', '2012-09-24 10:37:46'),
(77, 13, 'volunteers', 'Volunteers', '<p><font color="#ffffff" face="Arial"><font style="text-decoration: underline" class="whiteheader" color="#ffffff" face="Arial">VOLUNTEERING AT ST KILDA FILM FESTIVAL</font></font></p>\n<p><font color="#ffffff" face="Arial"><font color="#ffffff" face="Arial"></font></font>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><font color="#ffffff" face="Arial"><font color="#ffffff" face="Arial">St Kilda Film Festiaval is currently looking for enthusiastic, reliable and committed people to help us deliver Australia’s&nbsp;premier short film event.</font></font></p>\n<p><font color="#ffffff" face="Arial"></font>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><font color="#ffffff" face="Arial">As a volunteer, you will&nbsp;provide invaluable support to the Festival staff, filmmakers and audience and play a vital role in ensuring the successful running of the Festival.</font></p>\n<p><font color="#ffffff" face="Arial"></font>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><font color="#ffffff" face="Arial">Rostered volunteer positions are available through the festival period. Volunteers will be required to assist in various areas such as event assistance, ticketing, ushering and administration.</font></p>\n<p><font color="#ffffff" face="Arial"></font>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><font color="#ffffff" face="Arial">Please download the <a href="/Uploads/SKFF Vol Application Form 2011.pdf"><span style="color: #ffffff; text-decoration: underline">VOLUNTEER APPLICATION FORM HERE</span></a>.</font></p>\n<p><font color="#ffffff" face="Arial"></font>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><font color="#ffffff" face="Arial">Submit your completed form to <a style="color: #ffffff" href="&#109;&#97;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;&#58;&#102;&#105;&#108;&#109;&#102;&#101;&#115;&#116;&#64;&#112;&#111;&#114;&#116;&#112;&#104;&#105;&#108;&#108;&#105;&#112;&#46;&#118;&#105;&#99;&#46;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#46;&#97;&#117;" target="_blank">filmfest@portphillip.vic.gov.au</a>&nbsp;with ''Volunteer Application'' in the subject line. </font></p>\n<p><font color="#ffffff" face="Arial">If you have any questions, please call us on 9209 6490.<br />\n</p>\n</font>\n', '2011-03-16 14:03:41', '2011-04-06 10:52:19'),
(70, 13, 'soundkilda-entry-form-2011', 'SoundKILDA Entry Form 2011', '', '2010-09-23 13:04:25', '2010-09-23 13:04:25'),
(76, 13, 'entries-have-closed', 'Entries Have Closed', '<p><span class="orangeheader">ENTRIES HAVE CLOSED</span></p>\n<p>Entries for the 2011&nbsp;St Kilda Film Festival have now closed.</p>\n<p>If you film has been chosen to be screen as part of Australia''s Top 100 or in SoundKILDA, we will be in touch.</p>\n<p>If you have any queries in the meantime, please contact the Festival Office T: 9209 6490</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', '2011-01-31 09:25:46', '2011-01-31 09:28:28'),
(78, 13, 'trivia-night', 'Trivia Night', '<p><font style="background-color: #000000; text-decoration: underline" class="whiteheader" color="#ffffff" face="Arial">FILM BUFF''S TRIVIA NIGHT</font></p>\n<p><font style="background-color: #000000" color="#ffffff" face="Arial"><strong></strong></font>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><font style="background-color: #000000" color="#ffffff" face="Arial"><strong>Back by unprecedented popular demand!</strong></font></p>\n<font style="background-color: #000000" color="#ffffff" face="Arial">\n<p><br />\nJoin us for the launch of the 28th St Kilda Film Festival at this traditional and fiercely contested event.<br />\n</p>\n<p><strong><em></em></strong>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><em>Starring</em></strong> Melbourne’s trivia guru Alan Lovett from the Melbourne Trivia Company.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>A night to remember for casual filmgoers and hardcore buffs.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>WEDNESDAY 4 MAY @ 7PM<br />\nST KILDA TOWN HALL<br />\nCNR CARLISLE ST &amp; BRIGHTON RD, ST KILDA</p>\n<p><br />\nTO AVOID BITTER DISAPPOINTMENT GET YOUR GROUP TOGETHER AND BOOK NOW!</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>EARLY BIRD OFFER!</p>\n<p>Bookings before Friday 15 April </p>\n<p><strong>Tickets:</strong> $120 per table (teams of up to 10) inc. GST ($150 after 15 April)<br />\n$16 per individual inc. GST ($20 after 15 April)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Bookings:</strong>&nbsp;T:&nbsp; 03 9209 6266 OR&nbsp;<br />\nE:&nbsp; filmfest@portphillip.vic.gov.au<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Drinks at bar prices</font></p>\n', '2011-04-08 17:12:12', '2011-04-08 17:17:17'),
(79, 13, 'specifications-for-screening-copy-delivery', 'Specifications for screening copy delivery', '<style type="text/css">@import url(http://localhost/stkildafilm/callforentries/css/template.css);</style>\n<style type="text/css">@import url(http://localhost/stkildafilm/callforentries/css/template.css);</style>\n<style type="text/css">@import url(http://localhost/stkildafilm/callforentries/css/template.css);</style>\n<style type="text/css">@import url(http://localhost/stkildafilm/callforentries/css/template.css);</style>\n<style type="text/css">@import url(http://localhost/stkildafilm/callforentries/css/template.css);</style>\n<style type="text/css">@import url(http://localhost/stkildafilm/callforentries/css/template.css);</style>\n<style type="text/css">@import url(http://localhost/stkildafilm/callforentries/css/template.css);</style>\n<style type="text/css">@import url(http://localhost/stkildafilm/callforentries/css/template.css);</style>\n<style type="text/css">@import url(http://localhost/stkildafilm/callforentries/css/template.css);</style>\n<style type="text/css">@import url(http://localhost/stkildafilm/callforentries/css/template.css);</style>\n<style type="text/css">@import url(http://localhost/stkildafilm/callforentries/css/template.css);</style>\n<style type="text/css">@import url(http://localhost/stkildafilm/callforentries/css/template.css);</style>\n<style type="text/css">@import url(http://localhost/stkildafilm/callforentries/css/template.css);</style>\n<style type="text/css">@import url(http://localhost/stkildafilm/callforentries/css/template.css);</style>\n<p class="whiteheader"><u>ST KILDA FILM FESTIVAL 2012&nbsp;</u></p>\n<p class="whiteheader"><u><br />\n</u></p>\n<p class="whiteheader"><u>preferred screening and audio SPECIFICATIONS</u></p>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><u>35mm </u></p>\n<p>Dolby Digital or Dolby Stereo Sound</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><u>16mm </u></p>\n<p>Mono </p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><u>Digibeta (25fps) </u></p>\n<p>A Dolby Surround Mix (preferred) on Tracks 1&amp;2. Where a\nDolby Surround is not available a Stereo Mix should be on tracks 1&amp;2</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><u>HDCam SR (25fps) </u></p>\n<p>5.1 Discrete Mix on Tracks 1-6 in the format</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>- LEFT</p>\n<p>- RIGHT</p>\n<p>- CENTRE</p>\n<p>- LFE / SUB BASS</p>\n<p>- SURROUND LEFT</p>\n<p>- SURROUND RIGHT</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Where a 5.1 discrete mix is not available then a Dolby\nSurround mix should be on Tracks 7&amp;8</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><u>Blu-Ray (25fps) </u></p>\n<p>5.1 Discrete ONLY.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><u>35mm </u></p>\n<p>With either Dolby Digital or Dolby Stereo sound</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><u>Digital Betacam (25fps) </u></p>\n<p>With a Dolby Surround Mix (preferred) on Tracks 1&amp;2.\nWhere a Dolby Surround is not available a Stereo Mix should be on tracks\n1&amp;2.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><u>HD CAM SR (25fps)&nbsp;</u></p>\n<p>With a 5.1 Discrete Mix on Tracks 1-6 in\nthe format</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>- LEFT</p>\n<p>- RIGHT</p>\n<p>- CENTRE</p>\n<p>- LFE / SUB BASS</p>\n<p>- SURROUND LEFT</p>\n<p>- SURROUND RIGHT</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Where a 5.1 discrete mix is not available then a Dolby\nSurround mix should be on Tracks 7&amp;8</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<p><span class="whiteheader">DEFINITIONS:</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><u>Stereo </u></p>\n<p>A Mix with only Left and Right information - L/R</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><u>Dolby Surround </u></p>\n<p>A Mix delivered on NON film formats with Left, Centre, Right\nand Surround information encoded into 2 channels called Left Total and Right\nTotal – LtRt</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><u>5.1 Discrete </u></p>\n<p>A Mix delivered on NON film formats with Left, Right,\nCentre, LFE (Sub Bass), Left Surround, and Right Surround</p>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><u>Dolby Stereo </u></p>\n<p>A 35mm Film only format – Similar to Dolby Surround and in\nthe format LtRt</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><u>Dolby Digital</u></p>\n<p>A 35mm Film only format –with a 5.1 Mix and Dolby Stereo\nalso on the print</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>', '2011-10-18 12:51:40', '2011-10-25 09:50:28'),
(115, 19, 'frequently-asked-questions', 'Frequently Asked Questions', '<style type="text/css">@import url(http://localhost/stkildafilm/callforentries/css/template.css);</style>\n<style type="text/css">@import url(http://localhost/stkildafilm/callforentries/css/template.css);</style>\n<p>     	</p>\n<span class="page_heading">FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS</span><br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<span class="page_boldheading"><span class="page_subheading"><span class="">What films are eligible for the St Kilda Film Festival competition?</span><br class="" />\n</span></span>\n<span class="page_text">Only Australian entries are eligible for the St Kilda Film Festival competition. International entries will not be accepted for competition. St Kilda Film Festival is open to all film genres. If you are unsure if your film is eligible, please call Festival staff on 03 9209 6490 or email </span><a href="&#109;&#97;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;&#58;&#102;&#105;&#108;&#109;&#102;&#101;&#115;&#116;&#64;&#112;&#111;&#114;&#116;&#112;&#104;&#105;&#108;&#108;&#105;&#112;&#46;&#118;&#105;&#99;&#46;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#46;&#97;&#117;"><span class="page_text">filmfest@portphillip.vic.gov.au</span></a><br />\n<br />\n<span class="page_boldheading"><span class="page_subheading"><span class="">• What length of film may be submitted?</span><br class="" />\n</span></span>\n<span class="page_text">As the St Kilda Film Festival is Academy accredited, all films must be no longer than 40 minutes, inclusive of credits.</span><br />\n<br />\n<span class="page_boldheading"><span class="page_subheading"><span class="">• Can I submit a work in progress?</span><br class="" />\n</span></span>\n<span class="page_text">Works in progress may be entered. Indicate work in progress status clearly on the preview tape and please advise of expected completion date.</span><br />\n<br />\n<span class="page_boldheading"><span class="page_heading"><span class="">• What material should I submit?</span><br class="" />\n</span></span>\n<span class="page_text">1. Completed entry form<br />\n2. Payment completed via online service, or by cheque or money order (sent with preview disc)<br />\n3. Preview copy of film on DVD (please ensure DVD is not copy-protected, as multiple copies may need to be made for judging)<br />\n4. One film still to be used for promotional purposes (eg. Festival program and website)</span><br />\n<br />\n<span class="page_text">Stills must be submitted on a CD. Please ensure resolution is at least 300 DPI and as large as possible. Do not email your stills – the large files block up our inbox! Materials that are emailed will not be accepted.</span><br />\n<br />\n<span class="page_text"><span class="">Optional Material:</span></span><br />\n<span class="page_text">CV of the writer/director/producer<br />\nPublicity material (ie reviews, press kits etc)</span><br />\n<br />\n<span class="page_boldheading"><span class="page_subheading"><span class="">• Where do I send my entry?</span><br class="" />\n</span></span>\n<span class="page_text">Once the online entry form and payment have been completed, preview tapes and additional material should be posted to:</span><br />\n<br />\n<span class="page_text">St Kilda Film Festival<br />\nPrivate Bag No 3<br />\nPO St Kilda <br />\nVIC 3182<br />\n<br />\nOr delivered by hand to:<br />\nSt Kilda Film Festival<br />\nLevel 1<br />\n232 Carlisle Street<br />\nBalaclava<br />\nVIC 3183<br />\nEntries MUST be postmarked or received by 5pm, Friday 30 January 2015</span><br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<span class="page_boldheading"><span class="page_subheading"><span class="">• What is the entry fee?</span><br class="" />\n</span></span>\n<span class="page_text">For Individuals:<br />\n$33.00 including GST applies to each film submitted.<br />\nSchools and Institutions:<br />\n$132.00 including GST for a compilation of up to 10 films.</span><br />\n<br />\n<span class="page_text">The entry fee can be paid online once an entry form has been received, or by cheque or money order sent to the Festival office. Fees are non-refundable.</span><br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<span class="page_boldheading"><span class="page_subheading"><span class="">• What formats can be screened at the Festival?</span><br class="" />\n</span></span>\n<span class="page_text">St Kilda Film Festival will only screen productions finished on 35mm, 16mm, Digibeta, HDCAM, DCP (unencrypted) and E-Cinema. The Festival is unable to screen SP Betacam or DVD. <br />\n<br />\nTo ensure your film is screened correctly, you must include screening gauge and ratio details as requested on the entry form.</span><br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<span class="page_boldheading"><span class="page_subheading"><span class="">• When will selection be confirmed?</span><br class="" />\n</span></span>\n<span class="page_text">If your film is selected for the competition, you will be sent a letter of confirmation by Wednesday 1 April 2015. Film prints, tape masters, hard drives, USB or upload must then be received by Monday 13 April 2015.</span><br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<span class="page_boldheading"><span class="page_subheading"><span class="">• How will my screening copy be returned?</span><br class="" />\n</span></span>\n<span class="page_text">Hard drives, Digibetas and HD Cams will be returned to the nominated address on the entry form. USB submissions will not be sent back. Please be sure to update your return address with the Festival office if this changes.</span><br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<span class="page_boldheading"><span class="page_subheading"><span class="">• How do I contact the Festival Office?<br />\n</span></span></span><span style="color: #ece6f1; font-family: Karla, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 21px;">By phone on 03 9209 6490 or email at </span><a href="&#109;&#97;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;&#58;&#102;&#105;&#108;&#109;&#102;&#101;&#115;&#116;&#64;&#112;&#111;&#114;&#116;&#112;&#104;&#105;&#108;&#108;&#105;&#112;&#46;&#118;&#105;&#99;&#46;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#46;&#97;&#117;" style="font-family: Karla, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 21px;">filmfest@portphillip.vic.gov.au</a><br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2012-09-17 12:42:32', '2014-09-24 04:52:50'),
(114, 11, 'sponsorship', 'Sponsorship', '<style type="text/css">@import url(http://localhost/stkildafilm/callforentries/css/template.css);</style>\n<style type="text/css">@import url(http://localhost/stkildafilm/callforentries/css/template.css);</style>\n<style type="text/css">@import url(http://localhost/stkildafilm/callforentries/css/template.css);</style>\n<style type="text/css">@import url(http://localhost/stkildafilm/callforentries/css/template.css);</style>\n<style type="text/css">@import url(http://localhost/stkildafilm/callforentries/css/template.css);</style>\n<style type="text/css">@import url(http://localhost/stkildafilm/callforentries/css/template.css);</style>\n<style type="text/css">@import url(http://localhost/stkildafilm/callforentries/css/template.css);</style>\n<style type="text/css">@import url(http://localhost/stkildafilm/callforentries/css/template.css);</style>\n<style type="text/css">@import url(http://localhost/stkildafilm/callforentries/css/template.css);</style>\n<style type="text/css">@import url(http://localhost/stkildafilm/callforentries/css/template.css);</style>\n<style type="text/css">@import url(http://localhost/stkildafilm/callforentries/css/template.css);</style>\n<style type="text/css">@import url(http://localhost/stkildafilm/callforentries/css/template.css);</style>\n<style type="text/css">@import url(http://localhost/stkildafilm/callforentries/css/template.css);</style>\n<style type="text/css">@import url(http://localhost/stkildafilm/callforentries/css/template.css);</style>\n<table width="100%">\n    <tbody>\n        <tr>\n            <td style="vertical-align: top !important;" valign="top" width="340"><span class="page_heading">SPONSOR OUR FESTIVAL</span><br />\n            <br />\n            <br />\n            <span class="page_text">T</span><span class="page_text">he St Kilda Film Festival is Australia’s oldest and largest short film festival. <br />\n            <br />\n            Held in May every year, the Festival kicks off with an Opening Night ceremony to rival the Festival De Cannes, with more than 3,000 guests descending on the stunning Palais Theatre on the St Kilda Foreshore for a screening of Festival highlights. Guests then move to St Kilda’s iconic town hall, a century-old monument to classical revival architecture that hosts Melbourne’s premier opening night party each year.<br />\n            <br />\n            Over the following week, the Festival showcases the best and brightest short filmmakers in the Top 100 Competition Screenings, while Australia’s finest </span><span class="page_text">music videos are played on the big screen at the very hip SoundKILDA screening and party. Throughout the Festival, filmmakers are invited to network and explore their craft at a series of filmmaker development events. Then, on Closing Night, the Festival is wrapped up with a very festive awards ceremony and Closing Night party.</span><span class="page_text"><br />\n            </span><br />\n            <p><span class="page_text">The Festival has recently grown from six to ten days, with </span><span class="page_text">an expanded program including special event&nbsp;<span style="font-size: 14.4444446563721px;">screenings, additional filmmakers development sessions and anniversary celebrations.</span><span class="page_text">&nbsp;</span><span class="page_text">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n            <p><span class="page_text"><span style="font-size: 14.4444446563721px;">Don’t miss your chance to partner with this unique Melbourne event.</span></span></p>\n            <p>&nbsp;</p>\n            <p><img alt="" src="/stkildafilm/callforentries/Uploads/Sponsorship-Saffran-crop.jpg" width="340" height="479" />&nbsp;</p>\n            <span class="page_heading"><br />\n            SPECIAL BENEFITS<br />\n            <br />\n            </span><span class="page_boldheading"><span class="">As a partner of the Festival you can:</span></span><br />\n            <br />\n            <span class="page_text">• Increase consumer recognition and brand loyalty<br />\n            • Reach a targeted and savvy audience<br />\n            • Align yourself with an iconic Melbourne institution and the emerging stars of Australian Film<br />\n            • Stimulate sales and trial usage of products through creative sampling at the event<br />\n            • Demonstrate social responsibility and cultural involvement</span><br />\n            <p>&nbsp;</p>\n            <span class="page_boldheading">Key Partner Benefits can include:</span><br />\n            <p><br />\n            </p>\n            <span class="page_text">• Major site activations&nbsp;<br />\n            • Cinema TVC spots in Film Festival sessions<br />\n            • Logo recognition on Festival marketing collateral<br />\n            • Advertising in the Festival program and online<br />\n            • Sampling opportunities&nbsp;<br />\n            <span style="font-size: 14.4444446563721px;">• Commercial rights&nbsp;<br />\n            </span></span><span style="color: #ece6f1; font-family: Karla, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 21px;">• Corporate Hosting: give your VIPs, clients or staff a “money can’t buy” experience at a St Kilda Film Festival event</span>\n            <p><span class="page_text">\n            <br />\n            </span></p>\n            <p><br />\n            </p>\n            <p>&nbsp;</p>\n            <p>&nbsp;</p>\n            <br />\n            <br />\n            <br />\n            <br />\n            <br />\n            </td>\n            <td valign="top" width="20">&nbsp;</td>\n            <td valign="top" width="340">\n            <p><img alt="" src="/stkildafilm/callforentries/Uploads/Sponsorship-Bundaberg.jpg" width="340" height="440" /></p>\n            <p class="page_text"><span class="page_subheading"><span class="page_text"><br />\n            </span></span><span class="page_heading"><span class="">Where it''s at<span class="">\n            </span></span></span><span class="page_subheading"><br />\n            <br />\n            </span></p>\n            <p><span class="page_text"><span class="">St Kilda Film Festival is smart,  fun, creative and cool. It attracts more than 20,000 of Melbourne’s most  discerning film fans and industry practitioners each year, with 45% of our crowd aged between 25 and 45 years. They are curious  professionals with a median income of $70k+, large social networks and  active lifestyles. They could also be a fan of your brand.<br />\n            <br />\n            <br />\n            </span></span></p>\n            <p><span class="page_boldheading">You’re in good company</span><br />\n            <br />\n            <span class="page_text">Previous sponsors of the St Kilda  Film Festival include:  Renault, Simply Energy, Boags, Rekorderlig  Cider, Movie Network, TAC,  Kodak, Stella Artois,  Digital Pictures, Air Asia, Xanadu Wines,  Network 10, Music &amp;  Effects, Monkeesee, Inside Film and more… </span><br />\n            <br />\n            <br />\n            </p>\n            <p>\n            <img alt="" src="http://localhost/stkildafilm/stkildafilm/callforentries/Uploads/Sponsorship-Renault.jpg" width="340" height="510" /><br />\n            <br />\n            <br />\n            </p>\n            <p><span class="page_heading"><span class="">Contact us</span></span></p>\n            <p>&nbsp;</p>\n            <p>&nbsp;</p>\n            <p>&nbsp;</p>\n            <p><span style="color: #ece6f1; font-family: Karla, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 21px;">Meagan Scott<br />\n            </span><span style="color: #ece6f1; font-family: Karla, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 21px;">Sponsorship &amp; Marketing Manager<br />\n            </span><span style="color: #ece6f1; font-family: Karla, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 21px;"><a href="&#109;&#97;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;&#58;&#32;&#109;&#115;&#99;&#111;&#116;&#116;&#64;&#112;&#111;&#114;&#116;&#112;&#104;&#105;&#108;&#108;&#105;&#112;&#46;&#118;&#105;&#99;&#46;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#46;&#97;&#117;">mscott@portphillip.vic.gov.au</a>&nbsp;<br />\n            </span>\n            </p>\n            <p><span class="page_text">+61 403 844 266</span>&nbsp;</p>\n            <p>&nbsp;</p>\n            <p>&nbsp;</p>\n            <p>&nbsp;</p>\n            <p><span style="color: #ece6f1; font-family: Karla, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 21px;">Brad Elliott<br />\n            </span><span style="color: #ece6f1; font-family: Karla, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 21px;">Sponsorship Development Manager<br />\n            </span><span style="color: #ece6f1; font-family: Karla, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 21px;"><a href="&#109;&#97;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;&#58;&#32;&#98;&#101;&#108;&#108;&#105;&#111;&#116;&#116;&#64;&#112;&#111;&#114;&#116;&#112;&#104;&#105;&#108;&#108;&#105;&#112;&#46;&#118;&#105;&#99;&#46;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#46;&#97;&#117;">belliott@portphillip.vic.gov.au</a></span><span style="color: #ece6f1; font-family: Karla, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 21px;">&nbsp;<br />\n            </span><span style="color: #ece6f1; font-family: Karla, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 21px;">+61 478 487 719</span></p>\n            <p>&nbsp;</p>\n            <p>&nbsp;</p>\n            <p>&nbsp;</p>\n            <p>&nbsp;</p>\n            </td>\n        </tr>\n    </tbody>\n</table>', '2012-09-14 15:42:12', '2014-10-14 07:54:10');
